title: For Sale:  Steel Gun Safe
postcontent:
This nice big gun safe is welded up from plate steel. It's carpet lined and has four steel shelves that will hold the weight of anything.

It's 35 X 20 X 60 inches, with places for 9 long guns and lots of room for handguns, ammo and accessories.

It takes an ordinary padlock, but it has a hooded latch pocket to protect the lock and latch. There are holes in the back for anchoring the safe to wall studs.

I guess the main body is made of at least 1/8 inch plate.  I didn't build it.  I did mic the exposed edges and found that the latch hood is made of .130 inch steel, bent and welded; the long vertical of the shelves is .140, the shelves themselves seemed to be .129 to .134.  The side guards were pretty consistent at .134.  The hasp or locking bar is 1/4" with a hole big enough for a 5/16" padlock. The designer strengthened the common weak points of home safes.   All edges are doubled, and the door overlaps and pockets the safe opening by 1.5 inches.  The hinges are completely covered and protected against prying or punching.

Bring a come-along, a buddy or winch to load it.

$425 or best offer means that I am accepting offers on this safe, but before you lowball me, come and see it.

If you're reading this, then I still have the safe available for sale.

title: For Sale:  Lee .223 REM Deluxe Rifle 3 Die Set 90604 BRAND NEW IN BOX .223/5.56 223/556
postcontent:
Lee .223 REM Deluxe Rifle 3 Die Set 90604 BRAND NEW IN BOX. .223 5.56 223 556 AR-15 AR15 Mini-14

The Lee Deluxe Rifle 3 Die set is perfect for the beginning or experienced reloader. The set is made of steel and includes a full length sizing die, collet neck sizing die and bullet seating die. Use the full length sizing die to produce ammunition to factory-new specifications using cases fired in other guns. The collet neck sizing die will allow you to produce ammunition that is fire-formed to the chamber of one rifle.

Lee Precision has been producing some of the highest quality reloading equipment for over 50 years. Their Deluxe 3-Die Sets for rifle cartridges are no different. They are made to tight tolerances to help reloaders make consistent and accurate ammunition. These die sets are perfect for both beginning and seasoned reloaders. Each die is made of steel and the set comes with a full length sizing die, collet neck sizing die and bullet seating die. Reloaders use the full length sizing die to produce ammunition to factory-new specifications using new brass or brass cases that were fired in other guns. Full length sizing dies are also great for the reloader who wants to ensure each round loaded will chamber in their rifle with ease. The collet neck sizing die allows reloaders to product ammunition that has been fire-formed to the chamber of that rifle. Since only the neck is sized more force may be required to get each round to chamber but brass life is extended and a lot of reloaders see an increase in accuracy. This set also includes a bullet seating die, shellholder, powder dipper, storage box and load data.

Technical Information

Dies Included: Full Length Sizing Die Collet Neck Sizing Die Bullet Seating Die

Die Size: Standard 7/8"-14 threads

Shellholder Required: YES

Shellholder Included: Yes

Notes: Accessories Included: Powder Dipper Storage Box Load Data

title: For Sale/Trade:  AK-47 Upgraded Dragunov stock  -  MAK-90
location: Nippers Corner - South Nashville - Brentwood, Nashville, Tennessee
postcontent:
have a Norinco MAK-90 Sporter AK-47 rifle that I've decided to find a new home for. I'll be including two of the polymer 30rd mags. This is a great rifle, and everything is straight on it. The finish is good but not perfect. There are some of the expected handling marks on the finish. I have installed a dragunov style stock. It has been caringly broken in just enough to operate perfectly smooth and reliably, but certainly not worn out or abused. The bolt and trigger surfaces have been polished to insure that everything travels very smoothly. The double-hook trigger on these is superb. I have no problem maintaining a 3" group at 100-150 yards with cheap Wolf ammo. I did install a new complete recoil spring assembly last month. I have/had many different AK's and the Norinco models are among my very favorite. Unlike many other variants, the Chinese AK's haven't been imported since it was banned in 1994. There are a lot of them out there, but it does serve to make them more desirable and collectible than many other variants. Also, please be clear that the MAK-90 stands head and shoulders above any cheap Romanian, or any cheap piece of junk you've ever seen from Century Arms or IO. I also have 500 rounds of wolf non-corrosive ammo that I'll be selling separately for $250. It is sealed in plastic and in 20ct boxes.

MAKs are better than most AKs presently on the market in the U.S. because:

1) It is not a "parts" gun. It is 100% assembled in a foreign arsenal that has been making AKs for decades. This means no canted front sights or other shoddy workmanship. 2) It has a 1.5 mm stamped receiver where most AKs have a 1 mm. This means less heat fatigue in the weapon under hard use. 3) The barrel is thicker than most AKs. How much? Not exactly sure but the difference is visible to the naked eye. 4) The chamber and barrel are chrome lined. Why would anyone want a fighting rifle with out this vital combat feature? 5) The trigger is a double hook. This means a much smoother trigger pull than a single hook. There is no trigger slap. 6) It is selling for a lot less than the fancy Vegas Arsenal with comparable quality in everything but finish and cosmetics. 7) They were imported by the hundreds of thousands. You will be able to find plenty of parts and upgrades/accessories.


**I am willing to entertain reasonable trade offers. I won't respond to "Still available ?" emails. I'll remove the listing once it sells. Please assume it is available and ask your questions or make your offers. Phone numbers are also a very good piece of info to include if you are sincerely interested.**
